Solution Architect / Tech Lead
Oracle Fusion ERP & Hexagon EAM
Immediate start
Join Kinetic's large-scale transformation program!
About the Role

Join our team as a Solution Architect / Tech Lead for ERP & AMS, driving the architecture, integration, and continuous improvement of our Oracle Fusion Cloud ERP and Hexagon EAM platforms. If you have Maximo experience, we want to speak to you - the skills translate seamlessly into our Hexagon environment.

Key Responsibilities
Lead architecture for Oracle Fusion ERP and Hexagon EAM, ensuring scalability, security, and performance.
Translate business requirements into integrated ERP + AMS technical designs.
Own roadmaps, standards, and governance across Finance, Procurement, and Asset Management domains.
Guide SI and AMS partners, ensuring high-quality technical delivery.
Oversee deployments, integrations, upgrades, and data flows across ERP and AMS ecosystems.
Drive operational excellence, troubleshooting, and continuous improvement in BAU and project work.
Ensure compliance with SOX, GDPR, ISO13485,ISO27001:2013 and cloud-security frameworks.
What You Will Bring
Strong ERP architecture experience, ideally with Oracle Fusion Cloud ERP.
Experience with Hexagon EAM or IBM Maximo (highly transferable).
Deep integration knowledge (APIs, Boomi, OIC).
Solid understanding of cloud security, architecture governance, and enterprise design patterns.
Excellent communication and leadership skills across business and technical stakeholders.
Background in regulated industries.
TOGAF or cloud architecture certifications
Why Join Us?

You’ll have the opportunity to make a meaningful impact—shaping the future of talent, careers and people operations in a business that moves millions and enriches communities every day.

If you’re passionate about building diverse, capable workforces and creating pathways for future talent, we’d love to hear from you.

Apply today and help us move communities forward.

The Opportunity
I’m partnering with a Managed Services provider in Brisbane to find a Systems Engineer to join their technical services team. This is a hands-on role supporting and improving customer environments across Microsoft, networking, security, and virtualisation.

You’ll be working across Windows Server, Microsoft 365, Entra ID, Intune, Azure, firewalls, and backup platforms, using enterprise tooling to resolve incidents, improve systems, and drive operational efficiency.
If you enjoy technical ownership, structured environments, and real engineering work (not just ticket closing), this role fits.

What You’ll Be Doing
Triage and resolve incidents, requests, changes and problems via RMM and ITSM tools
Support Windows Server and desktop environments
Manage and support Microsoft 365, Exchange Online, SharePoint, OneDrive, Teams, Entra ID and Intune
Remediate alerts and failed backups (Veeam / 11:11) to agreed SLAs
Manage and improve toolsets including ThreatLocker, AlertOps, ConnectWise, PRTG, Backup Radar
Support and maintain virtualised platforms (VMware, Hyper-V, HCI)
Work with firewalls, VPNs, routing, switching and wireless (Cisco, Meraki, Fortinet)
Create KBs, SOPs and technical documentation
Drive efficiency through automation and better use of tooling
What I’m Looking For
3+ years’ experience as a Systems Engineer (MSP experience preferred)
Strong Microsoft stack experience – Windows Server, Microsoft 365, Entra ID, Intune, Azure AD
Virtualisation experience – VMware, Hyper-V, HCI
Networking experience – firewalls, VPNs, IPS, routing, switching, wireless
Experience with RMM tools for monitoring, patching and alerting
Working knowledge of ITIL and structured ITSM environments
Fortinet experience (NSE4+ highly regarded)
Microsoft certs desirable (AZ-900, AZ-104, MS-900, MS-102)
Clear communication skills
Full Australian work rights
What’s On Offer
Competitive salary
Career progression and certification support
Modern Brisbane office
Supportive engineering team and leadership
Real technical exposure, not just BAU tickets
Want to hear more? Please send your CV to Ryley at rladhams@humanisedgroup.com or call 0484 546 357

About Our Client

Our client is a leading, government funded organisation which is going through a large digital transformation. As key part of this evolution is scaling their current data capability to support their reporting, analytics, and emerging AI capability.

Role Purpose

This role will play a hands-on and highly influential role in designing, building, and enhancing the organisation's cloud-based data platform.

You will walk into an established snowflake platform, one fit for current purpose, but one being assessed, evaluated and subsequently redesigned for future use. This position will be key to shaping how the platform evolves to be fit for purposes, working closely with the Head of Data and key business stakeholders. You will be involved in vendor section and then management to enable you to scale a team and get the new platform up and running over the next two years.

This isn't a data architect position, but a senior engineer or team leader looking to step into a managerial role whilst remaining hands on technically. You will have a lot of involvement in scope and solution design, taking the lead in scaling and redesigning the platform.

This role is central to improving data accessibility, delivering high-quality data assets, and enabling analytics and advanced data initiatives across the business.

Due to the nature of the data, this role is only open to Australian Citizens, or those with Permanent residency who are on the path to citizenship.

Key Responsibilities

Data Engineering & Design

- Design and deliver scalable data pipelines and data models using modern cloud technologies.

- Build and maintain the organisation's data engineering layer within Snowflake and Azure.

- Develop robust ELT/ETL patterns across batch, CDC, event-driven, and API-based integrations.

Data Platform Delivery

- Oversee platform reliability, monitoring, optimisation, and lifecycle management.

- Ensure data assets are secure, trusted, and well-governed.

Vendor & Partner Management

- Work closely with external vendors and MSPs to ensure high-quality engineering outcomes.

- Provide guidance, technical direction, and quality oversight across delivery partners.

Analytics Enablement

- Provide strong data foundations to support business intelligence, analytics, and emerging ML/GenAI initiatives.

- Translate stakeholder needs into fit-for-purpose technical designs.

Capability Building

- Establish and document best-practice engineering standards and patterns.

- Play a key role in shaping and contributing to a future data engineering team.

Essential Knowledge, Skills, and Experience

- Hands-on technical experience with Snowflake, databricks, dbt, Python, and Tableau.

- Strong ability to design scalable data models and pipelines (without needing to be an enterprise architect).

- Practical knowledge of Azure data services and cloud-native engineering patterns.

- Experience working with ingestion methods including APIs, CDC, batch, and event-driven architectures.

- Familiarity with BI tools and semantic layers (Tableau or Power BI).

- Understanding of governance and metadata tools such as Microsoft Purview.

- Demonstrated vendor management and external delivery oversight experience.

- Excellent communication skills with the ability to simplify complex concepts.

- Experience working within agile, cloud-based engineering environments.

- Relevant tertiary qualifications or equivalent experience.

What's on Offer

- A highly influential role as a key hire within the expanding data function.

- Ownership of a modern, cloud-native data platform and engineering stack.

- Opportunity to contribute to the design and formation of a future data engineering team.

- Exposure to advanced analytics, ML, and AI initiatives.

- Flexible working arrangements (Sydney based).

- $170,000 - $190,000 inc super plus benefits

If you wish to apply for this position, please submit your resume by clicking the 'Apply Now' button. For further information please contact Mark Penn at Clicks IT Recruitment on +61 427 409 657.

From the beginning, we've led in inventing new technologies and entirely new industries. Today, we continue to lead because we have a world-class, diverse workforce that puts the customer at the center of everything we do.

The Role

Key responsibilities:

Develop BMS software, graphics, programming, and site-building

Tune PID loops and support commissioning teams with troubleshooting

Conduct site visits to ensure programs and graphics meet operational requirements

Configure system IP networks, including internet connectivity

Identify value-adding, cross-selling, and efficiency improvement opportunities

Communicate effectively and work collaboratively across teams

Participate in training, promotions, and cross-functional initiatives

Support a culture of continuous improvement and quality standards

Requirements:

Strong experience with BMS, HVAC, building controls, or automation systems

Background in managing or supporting technical teams

Experience with installations, commissioning support, and controls engineering

Well-developed analytical, reporting, and problem-solving abilities

Excellent customer service and communication skills

Highly organised, detail-oriented, and self-motivated

Able to manage multiple tasks and shifting priorities

Strong relationship-building ability and a solutions mindset

Benefits:

Attractive salary package + Full time permanent opportunity

Car allowance + mobile phone + laptop

Excellent job stability + Ongoing training and development opportunities

Inclusive work environment + Supportive management team

Our commitment to you

Our greatest assets are the expertise, creativity, and passion of our employees. We strive to provide a great place to work that attracts, develops, and retains the best talent, promotes employee engagement, fosters teamwork, and ultimately drives innovation for the benefit of our customers. We strive to create an environment where you feel that you belong, with diversity and inclusion as the engine to growth and innovation. We develop and deploy best-in-class programs and practices, providing enriching career opportunities, listening to employee feedback, and always challenging ourselves to do better. This is The Carrier Way.

Join us and make a difference.

Verification & Validation (V&V) Engineer – Defence Programs

Contract Length: Approx. 6 months
Location: Mawson Lakes, Adelaide (Onsite)
Security Clearance: NV1 required

We are seeking an experienced Verification & Validation (V&V) Engineer to support a Defence program delivering complex, mission-critical systems. This role is hands-on and suited to engineers who enjoy working across integration, testing, and formal certification activities in a structured environment.

About the Role

You will provide systems engineering support focused on verification, validation, and integration activities. Working closely with engineering and project teams, you will help ensure systems meet requirements and are supported by high-quality evidence suitable for formal acceptance.

Key Responsibilities

Conduct verification and validation activities, including authoring procedures, inspection reports, and analysis documentation

Support and participate in integration and test activities across complex systems

Develop, maintain, and update the Verification Cross Reference Matrix (VCRM)

Perform configuration reviews for hardware and software items

Establish and maintain end-to-end requirements traceability across specifications

Assist in the compilation of Objective Quality Evidence (OQE) to support system certification

Support management of Cameo and DOORS databases in line with requirements management plans

Raise Requests for Problem Resolution (RPRs) and support Engineering Change Proposal (ECP) workflows

Prepare formal test and verification deliverables for review

Essential Skills and Experience

Minimum 4 years’ experience in Verification & Validation or Systems Engineering roles

Strong hands-on experience decomposing requirements and maintaining traceability from requirement to test, result, and evidence

Experience working with tools such as DOORS, Cameo, Jira, and Confluence

Proven background in integration, verification, and validation of complex software systems and military hardware

Ability to produce clear, concise, and auditable verification evidence for formal acceptance

Desirable

Software development or automated testing experience

Exposure to Defence or safety-critical environments

Security & Location

NV1 security clearance is mandatory

Role is based onsite in Mawson Lakes, Adelaide

LANMAR supports defence maritime sustainment by delivering and sustaining analytics and decision-support capabilities within the Naval Logistics Information System (NLIS) ecosystem. In this role you will analyse stakeholder needs, design and sustain data models and ETL pipelines, and deliver trusted dashboards and datasets in a controlled Defence environment. Your work must be explainable and auditable – so that metrics and insights are traceable back to source data and changes can be deployed safely through structured governance.  

Key responsibilities: 

Analyse operational and stakeholder needs and translate them into data requirements, KPIs, acceptance criteria and lineage notes.  

Design and maintain SQL Server data models (staging, warehousing/presentation layers) 

Develop and sustain ETL pipelines (e.g., SSIS/TSQL and/or Spark/PySparkSQL), including reconciliation checks, data quality controls, and repeatable run procedures. 

Build and maintain Power BI dashboards and semantic models suitable for enterprise reporting in secure environments. 

Monitor and triage reporting/ETL issues; coordinate investigations and corrective actions with technical teams and stakeholders. 

Produce release artefacts and documentation required for controlled change (impact notes, test evidence, rollback considerations). 

Plan and support functional testing and user acceptance testing (UAT), including test scenario definition and evidence capture. 

Contribute to data governance activities required for future analytics uplift (e.g., documenting data flows, metadata, and candidate datasets for ingestion into enterprise analytics environments when directed). 

 

Skills/Experience 

Strong experience with SQL Server/T-SQL, relational data modelling and basic performance tuning. 

Demonstrated experience delivering Power BI reporting solutions (DAX, Power Query, modelling) 

Experience with ETL tooling such as SSIS (or equivalent) and implementing repeatable, supportable pipelines.  

Experience working in regulated or high-assurance environments (Defence, government, critical infrastructure) with change control and documentation.  

Desirable: SSAS/tabular modelling; asset management/maintenance operations. 

Desirable: Hands-on experience building and supporting Spark/PySpark pipelines (DataFrame/Spark SQL), including joins at scale, partitioning, debugging, and basic performance tuning (shuffles/skew/caching). 

Desirable: Experience working with Iceberg tables (or equivalent lakehouse table formats) including schema/partition evolution, merge/upsert patterns, and designing for governed access (e.g., Ranger-style RBAC/ABAC, audited data lineage). 

 

Security/Clearance  

You must be an Australian citizen and eligible to obtain and maintain an AGSVA security clearance (Baseline or higher). This role operates in secure Defence environments and requires adherence to Defence security policies, controlled change processes and audit-ready documentation.

About Us

With a focus on innovation and delivering better customer outcomes, there has never been a better time to work in the Tasmanian energy sector with Aurora Energy. Be a part of Tasmania’s energy future and make a strong contribution to the ongoing success of our business. 

We work hard to create a workplace that is welcoming and flexible, while balancing the needs of our people, the business and our customers. Our ‘Better Fit’ Program offers hybrid working after a training and/or probationary period to support work-life balance. 

Aurora Energy will invest in you with training and education, celebrate your successes through recognition and reward, and provide a range of employee benefits including an electricity discount, generous leave benefits, and support for your health and wellbeing.  

We believe that every employee has a role to play in contributing to a positive and supportive workplace culture. Our Aurora Way values have been created by our people, for our people. As an employee, you’ll use these values every day to guide your behaviours and actions. Together we’ll continue to make Aurora Energy a great place to work.  

This role sits within our Digital Transformation and Operations Business Unit. They are at the forefront of developing and rolling out new technologies, partnering with the business to solve complex problems, keeping Aurora Energy’s data and systems secure, and much more.   

They collaborate with stakeholders across Aurora Energy to understand problems and identify the best way forward. They take a team-based, people-centric approach. In their words: “There are lots of exciting things to do to support Aurora Energy’s digital transformation, and this breadth is what keeps it interesting.”  

Digital Transformation and Operations is made up of three parts. The Senior Data Engineer sits within Digital Operations.

Digital Operations is made up of an Infrastructure Team, Tech Contracts, Cyber Security, and Service Delivery. Collectively they make sure that all the technology we use in the business, including our systems and reports, is functional and well maintained. They also provide hands-on support for our in-house projects. They are known for being early adopters and champions of new technologies including GenAI.    

About the Role

As our Senior Data Engineer, you’ll lead a talented team and play a hands‑on role in building data solutions that support smarter decisions, better customer experiences and Aurora Energy’s digital future.

You’ll work closely with teams across the business to design, deliver and continuously improve our data and analytics platforms – while championing innovation, quality and good data governance.

In this role, you’ll:

Lead and mentor a team of data engineers.
Design and deliver scalable data and analytics solutions aligned to business goals.
Act as the go‑to expert for complex data engineering challenges.
Drive continuous improvement across our data platforms, tools and ways of working.
Champion agile and DevOps practices, collaboration and learning.
Partner with stakeholders, delivery teams and vendors to get outcomes across the line.

About You

You’re a technically strong leader who enjoys solving problems and helping others succeed. You’re comfortable balancing hands‑on delivery with strategy, and you’re curious about how data can create real value.

You’ll bring:

A degree in computer science or a related field, or equivalent experience.
Strong experience in data engineering, analytics and business intelligence, including cloud platforms.
Experience leading or coaching engineers or analysts.
Solid problem‑solving and solution‑design skills.
Confidence working with stakeholders in a fast‑moving environment.
Experience working in agile teams and a passion for continuous improvement.

Experience with Snowflake, cloud‑based data transformation tools or data governance frameworks is a plus. At least two years’ experience in a similar role is desirable.  

What’s on Offer

With a focus on innovation and delivering better customer outcomes, there has never been a better time to work in the Tasmanian energy sector with Aurora Energy. Be a part of Tasmanians’ energy future and make a strong contribution to the ongoing success of our business.

We work hard to create a workplace that is welcoming and flexible, while balancing the needs of our people, the business and our customers.

Our ‘Better Fit’ Program offers hybrid working after a training and/or probationary period. Our offices feature collaborative spaces, quiet pods, sit/stand desks, and meetings rooms of all sizes—all fully integrated with the latest collaborative working technologies and amenities.

How to Apply

If you have what it takes, please click ‘I’m interested’ or 'apply', ensuring you attach a cover letter outlining how your skills and experience are aligned with this role, as well as an up-to-date resume. Applications without a cover letter will not be considered.

You will be required to satisfy a National Criminal History Police Check. 

Applications close 9am Wednesday, 25 February 2026.
